    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="789"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2615.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your telegram of the 14th instant, which has been translated as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Ambassador of Mexico has just received instructions to ask your
                            excellency be pleased to interpose good offices to the end of obtaining
                            that Mr. Jose Barthelow, agent American authorities at Laredo, proceed
                            with all the activity case requires to execute orders; that he has
                            apprehension Mexican insurgents.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In reply, I beg to inform you that I have communicated your request to the
                    Department of Justice for its information and appropriate action.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
